content: - 4 -     I are honored to carry this message forward.  The economy benefits when we successfully tap   into the underutilized potential of more of our fellow Americans.5    Thank you, Janet, for everything that you accomplished as Chair and over a lifetime of   public service that thankfully continues today.  And congratulations, Ariel, for what you have   accomplished in service to others, which has made you such a deserving recipient of this award.                                                      5 Janet L. Yellen, “So We All Can Succeed: 125 Years of Women’s Participation in the Economy” (speech delivered  at “125 Years of Women at Brown,” a conference sponsored by Brown University, Providence, Rhode Island, May  5, 2015), www.federalreserve.gov/newsevents/speech/yellen20170505a.htm.
